Heightened Sense				KEY:Order Of The Lycan ~ Heightened Sense				CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Blood Hunter Class Feature.Class Feature.Order Of The Lycan.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Starting when you choose this archetype at 3rd level, you begin to adopt the improved abilities of a natural predator. You gain advantage on any Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on hearing or smell.
Hybrid Transformation			KEY:Order Of The Lycan ~ Hybrid Transformation			CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Blood Hunter Class Feature.Class Feature.Order Of The Lycan.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Upon choosing this archetype at 3rd level, you begin to learn to control the lycanthropic curse that now lives in your blood. As an action, you can transform into your hybrid form. This form lasts for 10 minutes. You can speak, use equipment, and wear armor in this form. You can revert to your normal form earlier by using an action on your turn. You automatically revert to your normal form if you fall unconscious, drop to 0 hit points, or die. The benefits of this form replace the rules for Lycanthropy within the Monster's Manual. You can use the feature twice. You regain expended uses when you finish a short or long rest. While you are transformed, you gain the following features.	DESC:&nl;FERAL MIGHT. You gain a bonus to melee damage rolls equal to half your proficiency bonus (rounded down). You also have advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws.	DESC:&nl;RESILIENT HIDE. You have resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage from nonmagical weapons that aren't silvered. While you are not wearing heave armor, you gain a +1 bonus to your AC.	DESC:&nl;PREDATORY STRIKES. Your unarmed strikes are considered a single weapon in regards to your crimson rite feature. You can use Descterity instead of Strength for the attack and damage rolls of your unarmed strike. When you use the Attack action tieh an unarmed strike, you can make another unarmed strike as a bonus action. Your unarmed strikes deal 1d6 slashing damage. This die increases to 1d8 at 11th level, and 1d10 at 18th level.	DESC:&nl;CURSED WEAKNESS. You have vulnerability to damage from silvered weapons.	DESC:&nl;BLOODLUST. At the start of your turn, if you've taken any damage since the beginning of your last turn, you must make a Wisdom saving throw to maintain control. The DC equals 10, or 15 if you have no more than half of your hit points left. On a failed save, you must move directly towards the nearest creature to you and use the Attack action against that creature. If there is more than one possible target, the DM chooses the target. Your turn immediately ends, and you regain control. If you are under an effect that prvents you from concentrating (like the Barbarian's rage feature), you automatically fail this saving throw.	
Stalker's Prowess				KEY:Order Of The Lycan ~ Stalker's Prowess			CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Blood Hunter Class Feature.Class Feature.Order Of The Lycan.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 7th level, your speed increases by 10 feet. You also can add 10 feet to your long jump distance and 3 feet to your high jump distance. In addition, your hybrid form gains the Improved Predatory Strikes feature.	DESC:&nl;IMPROVED PREDATORY STRIKES. When you have an active rite while in your hybrid form, your unarmed strikes are considered magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to nonmagical attacks and damage.
Advanced Transformation			KEY:Order Of The Lycan ~ Advanced Transformation		CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Blood Hunter Class Feature.Class Feature.Order Of The Lycan.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Starting at 11th level, you learn to unleash and control more of the beast within. You can now transform into your hybrid form as a bonus actions, and your hybrid transformation now lasts for up to 30 minutes. In addition, your hybrid form gains the Improved Resilient Hide and Feral Precision features.	DESC:&nl;IMPROVED RESILIENT HIDE. While you have an active crimson rite, you gain resistance to the damage type of your choen rite.	DESC:&nl;FERAL PRECISION. You gain a +2 bonus to melee attack rolls made with your unarmed strikes.
Iron Volition				KEY:Order Of The Lycan ~ Iron Volition				CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class	TYPE:Blood Hunter Class Feature.Class Feature.Order Of The Lycan.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Beginning at 15th level, you've honed your willpower to better resist the violent urges of your lycanthropic curse. Whenever you make a Wisdom saving throw to maintain control of your hybrid form, you do so with advantage. In addition, your hybrid form gains the Pack Hunter feature.	DESC:&nl;PACK HUNTER. You have advantage on an attack against a creature if at least one of your allies is within 5 feet of the creature and the ally isn't incapacitated.
